Maximum Subarray Sum - Kadane's Algorithm
Last Updated : 15 Apr, 2026
Given an integer array arr[], find the subarray (containing at least one element) which has the maximum possible sum, and return that sum.
Note: A subarray is a continuous part of an array.

Examples:

Input: arr[] = [2, 3, -8, 7, -1, 2, 3]
Output: 11
Explanation: The subarray [7, -1, 2, 3] has the largest sum 11.

Input: arr[] = [-2, -4]
Output: -2
Explanation: The subarray [-2] has the largest sum -2.

Input: arr[] = [5, 4, 1, 7, 8]
Output: 25
Explanation: The subarray [5, 4, 1, 7, 8] has the largest sum 25.

my 1st brute force approach
class Solution {
  public:
    int maxSubarraySum(vector<int> &arr) {
        // Code here
        int n =arr.size();
        int MaxSum=0,sum=0;//max=arr[0] because it may not check the negative part as 0>neg
        for(int i =0 ;i<n;i++){
            sum=arr[i];//as j==i its calculating it twice;
            for(int j=i;j<n;j++){
                sum+=arr[j];
            }
            if(sum>MaxSum){//only checking at the end making it go from left to right and not length wise 
                MaxSum=sum;
            }
            
        }
        return MaxSum;
    }
};

corrected brute force approach
class Solution {
  public:
    int maxSubarraySum(vector<int> &arr) {
        // Code here
        int n =arr.size();
        int MaxSum=arr[0];//or INT_MIN
        for(int i =0 ;i<n;i++){
            int sum=0;
            for(int j=i;j<n;j++){
                sum+=arr[j];
                MaxSum=max(MaxSum,sum);
            }
            
            
        }
        return MaxSum;
    }
};
complexity O(n^2)
Space O(1)

Kadane's algo says that if we are adding a big negative number to the sum the sum will decrease in such cases reset the current sum  
to 0 beacuse the subarray is continous;

class Solution {
  public:
    int maxSubarraySum(vector<int> &arr) {
        // Code here
        int n =arr.size();
        int MaxSum=INT_MIN;
        int sum=0;
        for(int i =0 ;i<n;i++){
            sum+=arr[i];
            MaxSum=max(MaxSum,sum);
            if(sum<0){
                sum=0;
            }
        }
        return MaxSum;
    }
};
complexity O(n)
space O(1)
